	}
},

graph: { 
	itemStyle: {
                 color: '#f2385a',
	},
        linkStyle: {
                 color: '#f2385a'
        }
}
```
These are correct. `normal` is removed

```
map: { 
	itemStyle: {
                 color: '#f2385a',
	},
	areaStyle: {
                 color: '#eee',
                 label: {
                    textStyle: {
                        color: '#c12e34'
                    }
              }
	}
},
```

About this part. Label should be in the same level with `areaStyle` and `itemStyle`. Also `textStyle` is removed. So it sould be:

```js
map: { 
	itemStyle: {
                 color: '#f2385a',
	},
	areaStyle: {
                 color: '#eee'
	},
        label: {
              color: '#c12e34'
        }
},
```

All these changes since 4.0 are trying to make `option` more flatten and cleaner.

This issue is labeled with `difficulty: easy`.
